location: Off the coast near the city of Rosh Hanikra.
summary: 10/09/1993: A terrorist riding a high-speed water scooter and armed with Kalashnikov rifles, pistols, hand grenades, knives and ammunition was "blown out of the water" by the Israeli Navy off the cost of Rosh Hanikra. Popular Front for the Liberation of Palestine (PLFP) claimed responsibility for the attempted attack.
gname: Popular Front for the Liberation of Palestine (PFLP)
motive: The attack was perpetrated in an effort to derail peace talks.
weapdetail: Kalashnikov rifles, pistols, hand grenades, knives and ammunition
scite1: Yigal Kotzer, ‘Navy Thwarts Attempted Attack,” The Jerusalem Post, October 10, 1993.
scite2: "The Silent Peace Partner,” The Jerusalem Post, October 10, 1993.
